  "review": "I'm surprised this movie got such a good rating.br br I enjoyed the film and watched it twice. It was funny and touching.br br But I'm not a fan of movies that portray disabilities in a way that portrays them negatively or as a source of comedy. This movie does both.br br There is no doubt that the lead character has severe physical limitations. There is also no doubt that this movie is sympathetic towards him.br br However, in the scenes where the character uses his disability to gain an advantage, or attempts to manipulate the situation for his benefit, the movie presents his actions in a negative light. For example, in the scene where he kisses his girlfriend and tells her she's disabled, it suggests that his affection is insincere, because he knows she will reject him. Or the scenes where he pretends to be disabled for laughs. As a viewer, you may laugh at his jokes, but it sends a message that it's acceptable to mock someone who has a disability.br br In addition, there are several scenes where the character is shown crying, which implies weakness. Weakness is presented as a sign of being disabled.br br If you watch this movie, I highly recommend watching it critically and identifying the instances where the movie is portraying the character's disability negatively.br br To me, this is a major flaw."  
}

