  "genres": ["Adventure", "Comedy", "Family"],  
  "review": "I just finished watching the movie 'Harry Was a Whiz.' The film tells the story of Harry Henderson, played by Christopher Lloyd, who is taken in by a giant monster known as Sasquatch. In reality, Harry is simply abducted by an escaped mental patient dressed in a fake Bigfoot costume. As the plot unfolds, Harry becomes convinced that he is a descendant of Bigfoot, which makes him unique among humans.br br The film starts slowly, and keeps pace throughout. Although many elements of the plot line are predictable, especially if you are familiar with the subject of Bigfoot, it is nevertheless entertaining. There are numerous scenes of comedy that I enjoyed, such as when Harry learns the meaning of the word 'monstrous,' and the scenes of the family trying to capture the monster.br br Unfortunately, several aspects of the film fell below par. For example, the character of Harry is rather boring. I felt that his personality was lacking in depth. Also, although the film was originally intended to be released in black and white, the producers opted to re-release the film in color. While this was done to appeal to a wider audience, I personally believe the film would have been much stronger in black and white format. Additionally, the actors' acting skills varied greatly. Some, such as Lloyd, were convincing, while others, such as Tom Hanks, failed to impress. Overall, I recommend this film, and would rate it a solid four stars."  
